{{Infobox person | name = Horst Brandstätter | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = June 27, 1933 | birth_place = [[Zirndorf]], Germany | death_date ={{death date and age|2015|6|3|1933|6|27}} | death_place = [[Fürth]], Germany | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | residence = | nationality = German | other_names = | known_for = | education = | alma mater = | employer = | occupation = Businessman | title = | salary = | networth = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | party = | boards = | religion = | spouse = | children = | parents = | relatives = | box_width = }} '''Horst Brandstätter''' (June 27, 1933 – June 3, 2015) was the owner of the [[Netherlands|German]] company [[Brandstätter Group]]. The company was founded by Andreas Brandstätter in 1876.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spiegel.de/wirtschaft/unternehmen/playmobil-firmenpatriarch-horst-brandstaetter-ist-tot-a-1037674.html|title=Horst Brandstätter: Playmobil-Patriarch ist tot|author=((SPIEGEL ONLINE, Hamburg, Germany))|date=8 June 2015|work=SPIEGEL ONLINE}}</ref>
==Early life== Horst Brandstätter was born on June 27, 1933 in Zirndorf, Germany.
==Career== Brandstätter joined the family firm in 1952.<ref name="register">{{Cite web|title = Life in plastic, it's fantastic: Playmobil supremo dies at 81|url = https://www.theregister.co.uk/2015/06/09/rip_horst_brandstatter_obit/|accessdate = 2016-01-02|first = Lester|last = Haines|date = 2015-06-09|website = [[The Register]]}}</ref> His support of the inventor [[Hans Beck]] allowed the company to begin production on what became the popular toy [[Playmobil]], prototypes of which had been developed by Beck at the company. The [[1973 oil crisis]] necessitated the creation of a toy whose production required little solid [[plastic]]; he had asked Beck for "the maximum amount of play value for the minimum amount of plastic".<ref name="register" />
==Death== He died on June 3, 2015 in Fürth.<ref>[http://www.goethe.de/ges/wrt/en1198396.htm Cheerful Plastic Figures from Franconia – Playmobil Conquers the Playroom], ''Goethe-Institut''</ref>
